}}

Throughout his career, Brewer has represented [[Canada]] at various tournaments. He first represented Canada as a member of the national junior team at the [[1998 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]] where he was named an [[Captain (ice hockey)|assistant captain]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Holden lifts Canadians into win column, finally|publisher=The Province|date=29 December 1997|url=|accessdate=2007-05-02}}</ref> Although eligible for the [[1999 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|1999 edition]] of the same tournament, Brewer was unable to play due to [[National Hockey League|NHL]] commitments with the [[New York Islanders]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Spencer |first=Donna |title=With more junior-aged NHLers, could Canada have won the gold?|publisher=Star-Phoenix|date=7 January 1999|url=|accessdate=2007-05-10}}</ref> On [[April 3]], [[2007]], Brewer was among the first five players named to play for Canada at the [[2007 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]] in [[Moscow]] and [[Mytishchi]], [[Russia]] from [[April 27]] to [[May 13]], [[2007]].<ref>{{cite press release|title=Five Players Named to Team Canada for 2007 IIHF World Men's Hockey Championship |url=http://www.hockeycanada.ca/2/4/0/7/4/index1.shtml|publisher=Hockey Canada|date=3 April 2007|accessdate=2007-04-08}}</ref> For the tournament, Brewer was named as the team's only permanent [[Captain (ice hockey)|assistant captain]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Gold medal hard to come by: Canada begins quest today against Germany|publisher=Winnipeg Sun|date=28 April 2007|url=http://www.winnipegsun.com/Sports/WorldMens/2007/04/28/4136611-sun.html|accessdate=2007-10-11}}</ref>

Overall, Brewer has represented [[Canada]] in the following tournaments:
*[[1998 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]]
*[[2001 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]
*[[2002 Winter Olympics]]
*[[2002 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]
*[[2003 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]
*[[2004 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]
*[[2004 World Cup of Hockey]]
*[[2007 Men's World Ice Hockey Championships]]

